  "local_port": 45566,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Are there any scholarships in MBBS program in Germany for Pakistani students?",
  "response": "Yes, Pakistani students can apply for various scholarships to pursue the MBBS program in Germany. Here are some options:\n\n### 1. **DAAD Scholarships**  \n   - The German Academic Exchange Service (DAAD) offers scholarships for international students, including those from Pakistan, to study in Germany.  \n   - Programs like the **Development-Related Postgraduate Courses (EPOS)** or **Helmut-Schmidt-Programme** may be relevant.  \n   - Visit the DAAD website for specific eligibility and application details: [www.daad.de](https://www.daad.de).\n\n### 2. **Government of Germany Scholarships**  \n   - The German government offers scholarships for international students through various programs.  \n   - Check with the German Embassy in Pakistan for updates on available opportunities.  \n\n### 3. **University-Specific Scholarships**  \n   - Many German universities offer scholarships for international students.  \n   - Examples include the **Heidelberg University Scholarships**, **Humboldt University Scholarships**, and others.  \n   - Check the official websites of the universities you\u2019re interested in for details.  \n\n### 4. **Erasmus+ Program**  \n   - Erasmus+ offers scholarships for international students to study in Europe, including Germany.  \n   - Pakistani students can apply if their home institution is a partner of Erasmus+.  \n\n### 5. **Charitable Foundations and Organizations**  \n   - Organizations like the **Konrad-Adenauer-Stiftung**, **Heinrich B\u00f6ll Foundation**, and **Friedrich Ebert Foundation** offer scholarships for international students.  \n   - These are often merit-based and may require proof of social or political engagement.  \n\n### 6. **Private Scholarships**  \n   - Some private organizations and companies offer scholarships for Pakistani students studying abroad.  \n   - Examples include the **HEC Pakistan Overseas Scholarships** or **Aga Khan Foundation Scholarships**.  \n\n### 7. **MBBS-Specific Scholarships**  \n   - While MBBS (known as *Medizin* in Germany) is a highly competitive program, some universities or medical schools may offer financial aid or scholarships specifically for medical students.  \n   - Research individual medical faculties for such opportunities.  \n\n### Steps to Apply:  \n1. Check eligibility criteria (academic performance, language proficiency, etc.).  \n2. Prepare required documents (transcripts, motivation letter, recommendation letters, etc.).  \n3. Apply directly to the scholarship program or university.  \n4. Ensure you meet the German student visa requirements.  \n\nFor the MBBS program in Germany, note that most medical programs are taught in German, so proficiency in the language (usually C1 level) is essential. Additionally, some universities may require the **TestAS** or other entrance exams.  \n\nFor more tailored advice, consult the German Embassy in Pakistan or the Higher Education Commission (HEC) of Pakistan.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
